I don't think that there...

240
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:04,797
...there's anything to worry about.
Come on, fellas.

241
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:08,913
I mean, do I look like a guy who'd run out
on a check? I mean, come on!

242
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:13,077
You guys!

243
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:15,475
Come on, Charlie! Come on, Charlie!

244
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,119
Yeah! Yee-hah!

245
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:22,834
What are you doing?!
I could've been killed!

246
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:25,315
You know you don't like
paying those things.

247
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:28,591
I still got the old wheels, don't I?
Did you see me?

248
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:31,109
You're pretty quick for an old guy.

249
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:34,953
The guy didn't get the license number,
did he?

250
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,798
Oh, Charlie.

251
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:28,951
- Where, Charlie? Here?
- 30 feet, 20 feet...

252
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:31,799
- We're almost... You missed it.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

253
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:33,353
Careful, careful!

254
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:35,994
Fine, all right. Just park it. Fine.

255
00:23:36,120 --> 00:23:38,953
Park it. Lock it. Let's go.
Just leave it here.

256
00:23:39,080 --> 00:23:41,799
- Charlie, where are you?
- Ow. I'm all right.

257
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:43,876
You all right?

258
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:48,679
- Save the burgers.
- The hamburgers. Charlie!

259
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:51,712
Where'd you go?
Watch out, there's a small cliff...

260
00:24:11,840 --> 00:24:15,310
- I'll fix you up.
- Anything. It's killin' me.

261
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:17,317
Thanks. Thanks a lot.

262
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:24,312
Hey, listen, you knock one over the fence
for your old man, all right? OK.

263
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:26,396
Tell Scott I love him.

264
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:28,916
OK. Great. Good. Bye.

265
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:35,230
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

266
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:40,756
Take half of it now, half of it later
and you'll feel a lot better. There ya go.

267
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:44,236
Remember, it's better to be a live dog
than a dead lion.

268
00:24:44,360 --> 00:24:46,874
I've felt the same way before.

269
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:49,195
- Good luck to you.
- Yeah, thank you.

270
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,556
Lulu?

271
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:06,436
Lulu?

272
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:09,120
- Oh. I'm sorry.
- What? Come here.

273
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:12,152
- What's that?
- Uh... well, it's, you know...

274
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:16,273
It took a while, but the whisky
caught up with me, I guess.

275
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,916
How can you drink that stuff?

276
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:23,153
I have to. My head's killing me.
I haven't had hard liquor in years.

277
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:35,831
Hair of the dog that bit you, babe.

278
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:39,550
God, no, no! Jesus, don't drink that!
No. I'm serious.

279
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:44,434
- You drank enough of it last night.
- Last night was last night.

280
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:46,437
- Here. Have some of this.
- No.

281
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:48,278
No, don't tell me no, please.

282
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:52,313
- This is better for you. It's tried and true.
- I don't want any of it.

283
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:54,351
- Do you have a hangover?
- Yes.

284
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:58,996
Then this is the stuff you drink
for a hangover. Come on. Drink it, please.

285
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:01,036
- No.
- Please.

286
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:01,876
- No.
- Please!

287
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,956
- No!
- Drink it!

288
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:12,036
Thank you.

289
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,831
Shit!

290
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:23,396
The guy at the restaurant
must have got the license number.

291
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:25,875
- Is this your car, pal?
- Huh?

292
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:28,673
I've been admiring your bike.

293
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:30,950
You interested in motorcycles?

294
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:34,517
No, I just like big things between my legs.

295
00:26:34,640 --> 00:26:36,596
Thank you, officer.

296
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:40,596
Damn, I left my suitcase in the car.

297
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:45,392
I cannot afford to get mixed up
in things like this! I got responsibilities!

298
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:48,592
Don't worry about the car.
It's gonna be fine.

299
00:26:48,720 --> 00:26:52,599
Oh, well, I am worried.
Let's just don't blow what we have here.

300
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:55,309
What are we... We gotta get that car back!

301
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,396
Just back off, Charlie!

302
00:26:57,520 --> 00:27:01,991
If you don't wanna hang around, go back
to your barbecues and your brunches.

303
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:04,953
We don't have to get the car back.
We can buy a new one.

304
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:07,111
520, 540,

305
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:09,708
560, 580, 600.

306
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:13,150
OK. Now, I need to see
some valid identification

307
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:15,635
and something showing
you have insurance.

308
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:19,355
- Can you take my word for it?
- No, I'm sorry. I'm afraid not.

309
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:21,756
OK.

310
00:27:22,840 --> 00:27:26,276
- How about Mr Franklin's?
- Now we're talking.

311
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:44,312
Come on, Charlie, talk to me.
What's on your mind?

312
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:50,470
You wanna know where I got the money
for the car, right?

313
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:54,553
I wanna know where you got that car,
that you can just leave it like that.

314
00:27:54,680 --> 00:27:57,148
Then I wanna know
where you got the money.

315
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:04,677
D- I-V-O-R-C-E

316
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:08,231
Equal distribution of assets.
It's a popular tune.

317
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:11,476
Oh, God, I'm sorry.

318
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:14,036
Don't be sorry. I'm not sorry.

319
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:20,311
Charlie, don't worry about that car.
It was still registered in his name.

320
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:23,352
You got to stop worrying so much.

321
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:35,359
- Hi! You guys want a ride?
- Thank you, thank you.

322
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:37,436
Hop in.

323
00:28:37,600 --> 00:28:40,433
- Here, let me...
- Welcome aboard.

324
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:31,436
Thanks for the ride.

325
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:36,276
Bye, Lulu.

326
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:39,271
- Thank you!
- Pleasure to meet you.

327
00:29:47,280 --> 00:29:49,236
Thank you, ladies.

328
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:56,792
Ladies, we need something
for the gentleman here.

329
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,956
Follow me.

330
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:10,756
Oh, Charlie!

331
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:13,796
- It's you.
- Forget it.

332
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:15,672
No. No. I will not buy this.

333
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:18,473
- Look at this.
- Absolutely, with all certainty, no.

334
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:22,479
- It brings out the blue in those eyes.
- Yes, but still...

335
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:24,955
- Ladies, what do you think?
- No.

336
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:26,911
Very nice.

337
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:28,549
Oh, God!

338
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:31,353
If you were my mother
and I presented him as my husband,

339
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:33,550
- What would you think?
- Very nice.

340
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:37,514
But I'd get rid of those handcuffs,
if I were you.

341
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:53,756
- Charlie!
- Oh!

342
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,516
Don't look so surprised.

343
00:30:58,160 --> 00:31:00,276
Get in the car.

344
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:16,517
- Where are we?
- Come here, Charlie.

345
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:22,036
- What are you doing?
- I'm setting you free.

346
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:25,709
- Maybe I don't wanna be free.
- Maybe you're not.

347
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,114
Come on.

348
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:29,357
Hello!

349
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:32,998
- Don't call me Lulu. Call me Audrey.
- Audrey?

350
00:31:33,120 --> 00:31:35,998
- Audrey! What a surprise!
- Hi, Mama.

351
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:40,314
Mom, I want you to meet
my husband Charlie.

352
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:43,238
- Oh. Well, hello, Charlie.
- Nice to meet you, Mrs, uh...

353
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:45,078
Just call me Peaches.

354
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:47,395
- That's her real name.
- Peaches...

355
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:02,190
- Here you are.
- Thank you.

356
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:05,869
Charlie, exactly how did y'all decide
to come down here?

357
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:10,674
Audrey just said "let's go visit
my mother", so here we are.

358
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:16,231
Audrey is very impulsive.
It's one of the things I like about her.

359
00:32:16,360 --> 00:32:19,511
And, dear, exactly when
did y'all get married?

360
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:23,155
In September.
We're still newlyweds really.

361
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:27,353
You'll have to visit us.
We have an extra room.

362
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:29,914
It's gonna be the baby's room some day.

363
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:33,271
Charlie fixed it up.
He's really good with his hands.

364
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:39,229
He wants a big family, but I think
just a boy and a girl would be nice.

365
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:42,477
- Don't you, honey?
- Whatever you want, honey.

366
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:46,673
See, Mama? He's just the kind of man
you always said I should marry.

367
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:23,073
Mama, we're gonna lie down for a bit
cos we've been driving all day.

368
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:33,078
- Why'd you tell her we were married?
- I wanted to make her happy.

369
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:36,954
- She doesn't know you were married?
- No. She didn't like him anyway.

370
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:39,753
Next time, let me know your plans.
I almost lost it.

371
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:44,032
That was part of the surprise. I wanted
to see if you could think on your feet.

372
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:45,957
How'd I do?

373
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:50,232
Like I said, you're a pretty good liar
when you wanna be, Charlie.

374
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:02,436
Audrey Hankel.

375
00:34:32,280 --> 00:34:38,276
The guy was, like, taking all the way. So
I'm running in like an idiot, and I slide in.

376
00:34:38,400 --> 00:34:42,518
Everybody's so surprised.
The catcher is holding the ball.

377
00:34:42,640 --> 00:34:45,518
I slide home, I steal home,
we win the game.

378
00:34:46,160 --> 00:34:47,479
Oh, God, it was great!

379
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:50,797
Well, I'm glad it was
such a good game for you.

380
00:34:51,080 --> 00:34:55,039
- This is good food too.
- Well, I expect you to eat it all up then.

381
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,912
You've got a real wife somewhere,
don't you, Charlie?

382
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:04,430
Uh, well,
that's a little complicated, Peaches.

383
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:07,711
- Do you love my daughter?
- I just met her recently.

384
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:09,796
It's kinda hard to...

385
00:35:10,160 --> 00:35:14,870
You take care then.
She's got some strange notions about life.

386
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:16,797
Yep. I know.

387
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:21,719
Oh, my gosh!

388
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:24,952
I had this dress in high school.
Mama saves everything.

389
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:27,469
- Don't you, Mama?
- Of course I do.

390
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:32,510
We packed a suitcase and I left it sitting
right by the door. I'm glad I had this dress.

391
00:35:32,640 --> 00:35:37,475
But poor Charlie's gotta wear what he's
got on the whole weekend. Poor baby.

392
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:45,797
Goodbye, Mama.

393
00:35:45,920 --> 00:35:49,276
We'll try and get down more often.
Charlie's job keeps him so busy.

394
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:52,517
Oh, I understand, dear.
Just come when you can.

395
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:55,151
- Give her a kiss.
- Goodbye, Peaches.

396
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:58,397
Come on. She's my mama, Charlie.
Give her a kiss.

397
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:02,394
- Bye, Charlie.
- Thank you for the meal. It was...

398
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:04,238
- Bye, Max
- Heads up, Max.

399
00:36:04,360 --> 00:36:07,875
- I hope things work out for you, Charlie.
- Good luck to you too!

400
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:10,195
It was wonderful meeting you, Peaches.

401
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:12,276
Here, let me...

402
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:19,356
Come on! Let's go.

403
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:25,399
- You wanna tell me where we're going?
- No.

404
00:36:27,240 --> 00:36:29,356
- So long!
- Bye.

405
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:31,357
I love you, Mama.

406
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:43,710
- Jesus, what's this?
- Get ready, Charlie.

407
00:36:44,240 --> 00:36:46,595
My high school reunion.
God, I'm so nervous.

408
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:48,676
Are you kidding me?

409
00:36:51,040 --> 00:36:54,077
Wait, wait, wait!
Who am I supposed to be?

410
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:57,156
- Oh!
- OK.

411
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:08,555
Am I supposed to sign in here?

412
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:12,189
- Audrey Hankel?
- Yeah.

413
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:14,277
Remember me? Donna Penski?

414
00:37:14,600 --> 00:37:16,830
- Yeah, sure, Donna. How are you?
- Fine.

415
00:37:16,960 --> 00:37:19,349
Audrey! James. James Williams.

416
00:37:19,600 --> 00:37:21,033
James! Hi!

417
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:23,720
How you doin'?
This is my husband Charlie.

418
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:26,388
- Hello, James.
- Pleased to meet you, Charlie.

419
00:37:26,520 --> 00:37:29,318
We have a booklet
with the names and addresses

420
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:31,908
of all the people
who weren't able to make it tonight.

421
00:37:32,040 --> 00:37:33,359
Oh, really?

422
00:37:33,480 --> 00:37:35,391
Audrey! Smile, please.

423
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:39,078
Thank you.

424
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:43,239
- I bet you've got kids, don't you?
- Mm-hm. Two, a boy and a girl.

425
00:37:43,360 --> 00:37:45,715
Oh, that's nice. What are their names?

426
00:37:46,400 --> 00:37:48,356
Their names?

427
00:37:49,720 --> 00:37:52,075
- Scott and Leslie.
- Scott and Leslie.

428
00:38:34,120 --> 00:38:36,076
Whooo!

429
00:38:50,600 --> 00:38:52,556
I want a big Badger yell.

430
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:54,796
Woo, woo, woo, woo, woo!

431
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:57,397
That guy's in my office!

432
00:38:57,520 --> 00:39:00,193
I've always been an introverted, shy guy.

433
00:39:00,960 --> 00:39:02,712
Charles Driggs!

434
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:06,594
Ah! God! No!
Uh, uh, uh... Just let me do the talking.

435
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:08,836
- Larry!
- What the hell are you doing here?

436
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:11,872
I thought you never got out of the office!

437
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:15,595
You remember my wife Peggy?
You met Charles at the Christmas party.

438
00:39:15,720 --> 00:39:18,951
Congrats on that promotion.
You really deserve it.

439
00:39:19,080 --> 00:39:22,993
- I knew you'd go right to the top.
- Thanks. That's nice of you to say.

440
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:25,759
I bet you say that to all the new VPs.

441
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:28,553
Uh, this is Audrey.
We've known each other for...

442
00:39:28,680 --> 00:39:29,749
We're lovers.

443
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:33,111
Only in the sense
that all human beings are... lovers.

444
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:35,276
Audrey Driggs?

445
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:38,119
I had to take his name for the baby's sake.

446
00:39:38,240 --> 00:39:41,312
- You're having his child?
- I think it's his child.

447
00:39:41,800 --> 00:39:45,110
Larry works in accounting,
down the hall from me, right?

448
00:39:45,240 --> 00:39:48,755
Is this the guy who would've wondered
why you were using company plastic

449
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:51,792
yesterday afternoon
in that motel in New Jersey?

450
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:56,958
Hell, Charles, we could've covered that.
Just let me know next time.

451
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:59,716
See?

452
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:01,393
This is my wife Peggy.

453
00:40:01,520 --> 00:40:05,308
We went to school together, Larry.
Remember? It's our reunion.

454
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:07,396
- Hello, Audrey.
- Hi.

455
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:13,312
Reunions are fun, aren't they?

456
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:15,237
Come on, Larry.

457
00:40:15,360 --> 00:40:17,316
Will you excuse us?

458
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:20,589
Driggs, I didn't think you had it in you.

459
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:22,916
Oh-ho...

460
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:29,555
- Thank you.
- Charlie!

461
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:32,195
- Charlie, relax.
- Relax?

462
00:40:33,040 --> 00:40:37,318
What were you doing over there?
That guy works in my office.

463
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:42,639
If he opens his mouth about any of this,
and, believe me, he will, I'm ruined.

464
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:44,796
Charlie, you are vice president.

465
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:50,558
Did you see the look on that guy's face?
He thinks you're a hero.

466
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:03,916
Charlie, what's wrong?

467
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:08,272
I'll tell you what's wrong. Company
plastic. Valid company credit cards.

468
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:11,153
They were in my wallet.
It was in my jacket. It's gone.

469
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:15,034
My MCI number, my access card
to get me into my own building!

470
00:41:15,160 --> 00:41:19,711
I mean, God knows who's got them!
My Christmas Club voucher... Oh, crap!

471
00:41:19,960 --> 00:41:22,679
- If I don't get it back, you know what?
- What?

472
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:26,916
I'm fucked!

473
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:31,036
Charlie, I got it.

474
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:34,076
I got your wallet.

475
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:36,032
You got my wallet?

