01:25:35,640 --> 01:25:37,471
Oh, thank you, Lord!

960
01:25:37,600 --> 01:25:41,309
Come in, come in.
Come, come, come! Come around!

961
01:25:41,440 --> 01:25:43,874
Come in! Come in! Come in! Come in!

962
01:25:52,000 --> 01:25:53,638
OK...

963
01:25:53,760 --> 01:25:56,957
I'll be back in a couple of days, OK?
You gonna be here?

964
01:25:57,080 --> 01:25:59,514
Did your sister really run off
with a Bible salesman?

965
01:25:59,640 --> 01:26:02,791
I swear to God. The religious types
are the worst kind.

966
01:26:02,920 --> 01:26:05,593
- I'll be back, OK? You'll be here?
- Mm-hm.

967
01:26:08,280 --> 01:26:10,714
OK, I better get going, all right?

968
01:26:16,080 --> 01:26:18,150
- Go on, go on. Go home!
- See ya.

969
01:26:18,280 --> 01:26:20,236
Hurry up. Go on.

970
01:27:09,560 --> 01:27:11,869
...can't do anything but fail.

971
01:27:12,000 --> 01:27:16,312
Did you see the SOS
Jesus COD'd to you?

972
01:27:19,280 --> 01:27:20,838
Are you saved?

973
01:27:20,960 --> 01:27:22,916
Are you good?

974
01:27:23,200 --> 01:27:25,156
Are you OK?

975
01:27:25,760 --> 01:27:27,716
It's late.

976
01:27:28,160 --> 01:27:30,116
Time to go.

977
01:27:30,240 --> 01:27:34,916
Thanks, Reverend Jim. It's 5 o'clock
right now, a. m., Baltimore time.

978
01:27:35,040 --> 01:27:36,996
We're comin' at you live.

979
01:27:51,920 --> 01:27:54,309
It's so strange.

980
01:27:55,000 --> 01:27:58,834
- Did you say something?
- I just don't wanna go to my apartment.

981
01:28:01,040 --> 01:28:02,996
Shit...

982
01:28:03,880 --> 01:28:05,677
Well...

983
01:28:05,800 --> 01:28:07,950
you can stay at my place.

984
01:28:08,080 --> 01:28:09,798
For tonight.

985
01:28:10,400 --> 01:28:14,552
There's not much in the way of furniture,
but there's plenty of room.

986
01:28:15,240 --> 01:28:17,196
OK, thanks.

987
01:28:30,520 --> 01:28:32,476
Audrey Hankel.

988
01:28:47,520 --> 01:28:50,478
Yeah, uh... Stony Brook.

989
01:28:51,640 --> 01:28:53,710
Charles Driggs.

990
01:28:53,840 --> 01:28:56,400
Yeah, with a D. D-R, yeah.

991
01:28:56,520 --> 01:28:58,795
Lemme have the address on that.

992
01:28:58,920 --> 01:29:02,435
1427 Maple. 1427 Maple. Thanks.

993
01:29:51,520 --> 01:29:54,876
- Where's the bathroom?
- Down the hall, to the left.

994
01:30:37,000 --> 01:30:38,956
Charlie...

995
01:30:44,680 --> 01:30:45,954
Yeah?

996
01:30:46,080 --> 01:30:50,915
What are you gonna do now you've seen
how the other half lives?

997
01:30:51,040 --> 01:30:52,996
The other half?

998
01:30:53,120 --> 01:30:55,076
The other half of you.

999
01:31:29,680 --> 01:31:31,432
Hiya, Charlie.

1000
01:31:31,680 --> 01:31:32,635
Ray!

1001
01:31:40,640 --> 01:31:42,596
Get up!

1002
01:31:46,280 --> 01:31:48,919
Let's see what you're made of now,
Charlie!

1003
01:31:49,720 --> 01:31:51,676
Charlie?

1004
01:31:53,200 --> 01:31:55,156
Charlie?

1005
01:31:55,600 --> 01:31:57,272
Ray, stop it! You'll kill him!

1006
01:31:57,400 --> 01:31:59,356
I'm just warming up!

1007
01:32:00,280 --> 01:32:02,236
Get out of the way!

1008
01:32:02,960 --> 01:32:04,518
Ow!

1009
01:32:05,640 --> 01:32:09,110
I'm glad to see you finally
made it to the suburbs, bitch!

1010
01:32:11,800 --> 01:32:13,392
Come here!

1011
01:32:17,320 --> 01:32:19,276
I don't care...

1012
01:32:20,520 --> 01:32:24,149
what she tells you, I know my wife.

1013
01:32:24,760 --> 01:32:28,389
And you white-bread VIP types
just don't do it for her.

1014
01:32:28,960 --> 01:32:32,669
- You all right there, Charlie?
- Charlie, I'm gonna get help!

1015
01:32:36,840 --> 01:32:38,512
Charlie!

1016
01:32:39,040 --> 01:32:41,873
Didn't I tell you to stay?
Haven't you hurt me enough?

1017
01:32:42,000 --> 01:32:44,673
Look what you're doing to me!
Get in here!

1018
01:32:45,720 --> 01:32:47,870
Why are you doing this to me? Shut up!

1019
01:32:50,920 --> 01:32:54,959
Come on in here, Charlie!
Come on into your bedroom, Charlie!

1020
01:32:57,640 --> 01:32:59,471
Lulu!

1021
01:33:00,760 --> 01:33:02,955
Stop it, Ray! Stop it!

1022
01:33:03,120 --> 01:33:04,758
Charlie, are you OK?

1023
01:33:05,000 --> 01:33:06,718
Charlie!

1024
01:33:12,840 --> 01:33:15,070
- I hate you!
- I hate you too!

1025
01:33:15,240 --> 01:33:17,196
- Lulu!
- Charlie!

1026
01:33:20,640 --> 01:33:23,074
Charlie, come here! I got somethin' for ya!

1027
01:33:23,200 --> 01:33:26,590
Why can't you just give me a chance?
Why?! Why?!

1028
01:33:30,600 --> 01:33:32,955
Stop it! Stop it!

1029
01:33:34,480 --> 01:33:36,550
No, no...

1030
01:34:16,080 --> 01:34:18,913
Oh... Oh, God!

1031
01:34:27,920 --> 01:34:28,989
Ray!

1032
01:34:29,120 --> 01:34:31,076
No! No!

1033
01:34:32,360 --> 01:34:34,316
No!

1034
01:34:38,280 --> 01:34:41,431
I hate you so much! Stop it!

1035
01:34:42,360 --> 01:34:43,349
Charlie!

1036
01:34:43,480 --> 01:34:44,595
No, Ray!

1037
01:35:05,640 --> 01:35:07,915
Shit, Charlie.

1038
01:36:18,360 --> 01:36:21,796
I understand that the break-in
occurred an hour ago.

1039
01:36:21,920 --> 01:36:23,876
- Yeah.
- Keys.

1040
01:36:24,800 --> 01:36:26,756
He smashed a window to gain entrance

1041
01:36:26,880 --> 01:36:31,271
and you were forcibly led into the house,
Mr Driggs, through the back.

1042
01:36:31,400 --> 01:36:34,790
I understand that he manacled you
at that time.

1043
01:36:35,000 --> 01:36:37,070
Mr Driggs, did you know him?

1044
01:36:37,640 --> 01:36:39,596
Did you know the guy?

1045
01:36:43,240 --> 01:36:45,435
He was my husband.

1046
01:36:45,560 --> 01:36:47,437
Your husband?

1047
01:36:47,560 --> 01:36:49,391
Ray Sinclair.

1048
01:36:49,520 --> 01:36:51,670
And what is your name?

1049
01:36:51,800 --> 01:36:53,358
Audrey.

1050
01:36:53,680 --> 01:36:56,194
Audrey, you wanna
come with me, please?

1051
01:37:00,920 --> 01:37:02,638
Wait.

1052
01:37:03,080 --> 01:37:05,799
You're not...
You're not taking her away because...

1053
01:37:05,920 --> 01:37:10,198
It's all right. It's OK, Mr Driggs.
We just need to get more information.

1054
01:38:02,600 --> 01:38:04,556
Charles?

1055
01:38:04,880 --> 01:38:06,598
Larry!

1056
01:38:06,720 --> 01:38:08,551
Hi.

1057
01:38:11,840 --> 01:38:13,796
Listen, uh...

1058
01:38:14,920 --> 01:38:17,150
We're all real sorry about your leaving.

1059
01:38:17,280 --> 01:38:18,793
Oh, that's nice.

1060
01:38:18,920 --> 01:38:21,115
There's no way to get you
to change your mind?

1061
01:38:21,240 --> 01:38:23,913
No. Nope, I don't think so, no.

1062
01:38:24,640 --> 01:38:28,269
- Is there anything I can do?
- No. Everything's been taken care of.

1063
01:38:28,400 --> 01:38:30,356
Everything's fine.

1064
01:38:30,920 --> 01:38:32,672
Well...

1065
01:38:34,080 --> 01:38:35,399
Hey!

1066
01:38:42,120 --> 01:38:44,588
How do you figure
a guy like Ray Sinclair?

1067
01:38:56,960 --> 01:38:58,757
Well...

1068
01:38:58,960 --> 01:39:00,996
Stay in touch. Promise?

1069
01:39:01,280 --> 01:39:02,759
Promise.

1070
01:39:06,320 --> 01:39:07,878
Hey, Larry.

1071
01:39:08,000 --> 01:39:10,673
It's better to be a live dog
than a dead lion.

1072
01:39:11,880 --> 01:39:14,440
It's been good working with you, Charlie.

1073
01:39:53,200 --> 01:39:55,236
Who is it?

1074
01:39:57,760 --> 01:40:01,958
I'm looking for the woman in 3F.
Lulu is her name, or Audrey.

1075
01:40:02,600 --> 01:40:05,672
I'm in 3F. You must want
the girl that moved out.

1076
01:40:05,800 --> 01:40:08,439
Uh... did you talk to her?
I mean, did she say...

1077
01:40:08,560 --> 01:40:12,155
Did she say where she was goin',
or a forwarding address or anything?

1078
01:40:12,280 --> 01:40:14,589
No. I moved in, it was empty.

1079
01:40:14,720 --> 01:40:16,676
OK, thanks.

1080
01:40:17,960 --> 01:40:20,110
- Hey!
- Yeah?

1081
01:40:20,240 --> 01:40:24,153
- Do you know what her rent was?
- Her rent?

1082
01:40:24,280 --> 01:40:28,910
Yeah. This building is rent-stabilised,
but I think the landlord is screwing me.

1083
01:40:30,600 --> 01:40:32,875
Yeah, well, it wouldn't surprise me.

1084
01:41:10,440 --> 01:41:13,193
The MP would grab 'em
and confiscate 'em,

1085
01:41:13,320 --> 01:41:16,118
and I'd take 'em back
and I'd sell 'em again.

1086
01:41:22,880 --> 01:41:25,474
- Here's your check, sir.
- Oh, thank you.

1087
01:41:53,240 --> 01:41:56,869
Hey! You didn't pay for your food.
Where you think you're goin'?

1088
01:41:58,120 --> 01:42:00,475
- Come on, mister. I haven't got all day.
- What?

1089
01:42:00,600 --> 01:42:04,912
- You didn't pay for your food.
- Sure I paid, Dottie. I put $5 on the table.

1090
01:42:05,040 --> 01:42:06,598
Do you think I'm stupid?

1091
01:42:06,720 --> 01:42:11,111
Look, it's a mistake. It was a $3.15 bill,
I left $5 on the table. That's a healthy tip.

1092
01:42:11,240 --> 01:42:15,950
- Do you expect to eat and not pay?
- All right. It's not that big a deal to me.

1093
01:42:31,600 --> 01:42:35,149
- Keep the, uh... keep the change.
- Sure.

1094
01:42:48,640 --> 01:42:50,835
You never said goodbye.

1095
01:42:52,440 --> 01:42:54,715
I never wanted to say goodbye.

1096
01:42:59,680 --> 01:43:01,716
Want a ride?

1097
01:43:11,240 --> 01:43:13,231
Sure, Audrey.

1098
01:43:13,360 --> 01:43:15,112
Why not?
